API -> set of rules and protocols that allows software applications to communicate
REST -> style that uses http methods
GET -> retrieve , URL , Limited 
POST -> add , request body

stateless -> no state management in server side 
Server doesn't store any client context between requests. 
payload -> data sent in request or response body

headers -> key value    
            contains meta data about request

content type -> to specify the type of data sent
    Content-Type: application/json -> default
    Content-Type: multipart/form-data -> file 
    especially -> POST, PUT, PATCH 
Accept -> tell server which form data client expects
 query parameter -> key value pair added to url (optional)
 path parameter -> url for specific id (mandatory)
 
CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) allows a server to specify which domains are allowed 
to access its resources. 
    use data from same Origin

JWT ->
    Header: Token type & algorithm 
    • Payload: User data (claims) 
    • Signature: Verifies token integrity
Bearer token is sent in request header